# OCS Phase 3 Design Specification

## 1. Workflow Diagram (Logic)
This section defines the logical flow of the OCS phases, represented as nodes and directed edges.

### Nodes
- **N1**: Phase 1: Initialization & Goal Definition (Director, Lyra)
- **N2**: Phase 2: Task Decomposition & Prompt Engineering (GPTASe, uTASe, puTASe, Lyra)
- **N3**: Phase 3: Design & Implementation (Aurora, Kodax)
- **N4**: Phase 4: Execution & Monitoring (Director, Agents)
- **N5**: Phase 5: Meta-Communication (Director)
- **N6**: Phase 6: KickLang Integration (System)

### Edges
- **E1**: N1 -> N2 [label="Goal Defined"]
- **E2**: N2 -> N3 [label="TASs & Prompts Ready"]
- **E3**: N3 -> N4 [label="System Designed & Built"]
- **E4**: N4 -> N4 [label="Loop: Refine & Re-execute"]
- **E5**: N4 -> N5 [label="Report Progress"]
- **E6**: N4 -> N6 [label="Update Knowledge Graph"]

## 2. UI Components
This section defines the core user interface components required for interaction with the OCS.

### 2.1 Task Assignment Interface
**Role Access**: GPTASe, TASe, uTASe, puTASe, Director
**Description**: A dashboard for inputting high-level goals, viewing decomposed tasks, and assigning them to agents.

#### Components:
- **Input_Goal**: Text area for "High-Level Objective".
- **List_TAS**: Dynamic list view for extracted Task-Agnostic Steps (TASs).
- **Control_Actions**:
    - `[Purify]`: Triggers puTASe to refine the list.
    - `[Assign]`: Opens a modal to select an agent for a specific TAS.
    - `[Execute]`: Initiates the workflow for selected items.
- **Status_Indicator**: Badges showing "Pending", "Active", "Completed", "Failed".

### 2.2 Progress Tracking Dashboard
**Role Access**: Director, User
**Description**: A centralized view to monitor the real-time status of the orchestration.

#### Components:
- **Tree_View**: A hierarchical visualization of Phases (Roots) and Tasks (Nodes).
- **Log_Stream**: A scrolling console showing live output from agents (e.g., "Director: Evaluating state...").
- **KPI_Panel**:
    - `Tasks Completed`: Integer.
    - `Active Agents`: Integer.
    - `System Health`: Percentage/Color (Green/Yellow/Red).
- **Resource_Monitor**: Visualization of API token usage and latency.

### 2.3 Output Validation Panel
**Role Access**: Deliverable Integrator (Director/Kodax)
**Description**: A tool for reviewing and validating the artifacts produced by agents before finalization.

#### Components:
- **Split_View**:
    - Left Pane: "Requirement/Source TAS" (Read-only).
    - Right Pane: "Generated Artifact" (Editable).
- **Checklist**:
    - `[ ] SMART Criteria Met`
    - `[ ] Style Guide Compliant`
    - `[ ] Logical Consistency`
- **Decision_Controls**:
    - `[Approve]`: Marks task as complete and proceeds.
    - `[Reject]`: Opens feedback dialog to send back to agent.
    - `[Refine]`: Triggers a "Refinement Loop" (Subtask).

## 3. Aesthetics
This section defines the visual identity of the OCS interfaces.

### 3.1 Color Palette
- **Backgrounds**:
    - `Slate-900` (#0F172A): Global Background.
    - `Slate-800` (#1E293B): Card/Panel Background.
- **Text**:
    - `Slate-50` (#F8FAFC): Primary Text.
    - `Slate-400` (#94A3B8): Secondary/Label Text.
- **Accents**:
    - `Sky-400` (#38BDF8): Primary Action / Highlight.
    - `Indigo-500` (#6366F1): Active State / Focus.
- **Status**:
    - `Green-500` (#22C55E): Success / Completed.
    - `Yellow-500` (#EAB308): Warning / In-Progress.
    - `Red-500` (#EF4444): Error / Failed.

### 3.2 Typography
- **Headings**: `Inter` (Bold, 700) - Clean, modern sans-serif for structure.
- **Body**: `Roboto` (Regular, 400) - Readable sans-serif for content.
- **Code/Data**: `Fira Code` (Medium, 500) - Monospaced with ligatures for KickLang snippets and logs.

### 3.3 Layout Principles
- **Grid System**: 12-column fluid grid.
- **Spacing**: 8pt grid system (8px, 16px, 24px, 32px).
- **Glassmorphism**: Subtle usage on overlays (background-blur: 10px, opacity: 0.8) for depth.
- **Border Radius**: 8px (Small components), 16px (Cards/Containers).
